  "text": "We distinguish two validation types: (1) Content-Driven Validation C C contains the set of constraints ensuring that the data is consistent with the intended syntax, semantics, and integrity of given data models. [CITATION_1] Technology-Driven Validation C T includes the set of constraints which can be generated automatically out of data models, such as cardinality restrictions, universal and existential quantifications, domains, and ranges. We determined the default severity level (corresponds to requirement R-158 ) for each constraint to indicate how serious the violation of the constraint is. We propose an extensible metric to measure the continuum of severity levels ranging from SL 0 (informational) via SL 1 (warning) to SL 2 (error). Although we provide default severity levels for each constraint, users should be able to specify severity levels of constraints they need to validate for their individual use cases, i.e., users should be able to define use case specific severity levels for constraints.",
